text:
A tiny Prince George showed no signs of fear while staring down an Australian bilby with parents Prince William and Kate Middleton in 2014.

Prince William, Kate Middleton, and Prince George visited Australia in 2014. David Gray/AFP via Getty Images

George was less than a year old when he embarked on his first royal tour to New Zealand and Australia alongside his parents, William and Middleton.

But for being so tiny, photos of him pulling funny faces at a bilby – a desert-dwelling marsupial – while visiting Sydney Zoo show prove he was anything but shy. George looked to be growling at the bilby while Middleton and William smiled on.

According to Vanity Fair, the bilby was actually named George, after the young prince.
